Tshidi Madia, News24Julius Malema (Lisa Hnatowicz, Netwerk24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories The EFF and DA are applicants in a case to have the so-called state capture report released to the public.WATCHPretoria &ndash; EFF leader Julius Malema has praised the courts following an order that opposition parties can intervene in President Jacob Zuma&rsquo;s bid to stop the release of the &ldquo;state capture&rdquo; report. &ldquo;The courts have demonstrated once more that our Constitution and the law do not have loopholes for criminals,&rdquo; he told hundreds of supporters who had spent Tuesday demonstrating outside the North Gauteng High Court in Pretoria.&nbsp;&ldquo;There will be no Mickey Mouse that is going to stop the report,&rdquo; Malema said.A full bench ruled that the EFF, Cope, UDM, and DA had vested interest in the investigation of the Gupta family&rsquo;s alleged undue influence on President Jacob Zuma.&nbsp;The merits of Zuma&rsquo;s changed application would be argued in court on Wednesday.&nbsp; The judges also struck off the roll Co-operative Governance Minister Des van Rooyen&rsquo;s application for an interdict.&nbsp;&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.